org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.ui

Class JavaScriptElementLabels

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.wst.jsdt.ui.JavaScriptElementLabels

  • public class JavaScriptElementLabels
extends java.lang.Object
    JavaScriptElementLabels provides helper methods to render names of JavaScript elements. Provisional API: This class/interface is part of an interim API that is still under development and expected to change significantly before reaching stability. It is being made available at this early stage to solicit feedback from pioneering adopters on the understanding that any code that uses this API will almost certainly be broken (repeatedly) as the API evolves.

                                            long flags)
        Returns the label of the given object. The object must be of type IJavaScriptElement or adapt to IWorkbenchAdapter. The empty string is returned if the element type is not known.
        Parameters:

        flags - The rendering flags
        Returns:
